        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Netted kelp is great for fire. Blue diamond stuff is great for plusses to all. Velious has a ton of cheap cold resist stuff you can hunt for of level 30ish mobs.</P><P>Probably your first move would be to get two diamond velium rings and two blue diamond bracers. Will really bite your other stats in the ass but that comes out to about +40 to all saves.</P><P>Other really cheap stuff you could dig up could be:</P><P>Giant Needlite wing (+4 to dis/mag/poi)<BR>rygor cloak (10cold/5mag)<BR>sparkling soul necklace (5dis/mag/poi)<BR>student's homework (10mag)<BR>many of the loam encrusted pieces<BR>froglok bonecaster's robe (10fire/mag)</P><P>And so on. Best bet is to head to bazaar and shop around, setting the filter for a particular save you're looking to buff up.</P><P>If you're a bit more wealthy you can try to pick up a necklace of superiority (+5 to all saves), and/or multiquest some of the velious armors.</P><P>One other thing you can do to beef up resists is finish your epic.. it has some good resists on it.</P><P><a href="http://tru7h.org/absor/" target="_blank">http://tru7h.org/absor/</a> -  ask absor anything!<BR><a href="http://xzzy.org/ereet/" target="_blank">http://xzzy.org/ereet/</a><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
